# Commands:

#                      probably flawed

#           UHAN    = filter using UniHan base: no Chinese in Unicode → use Japanese etc

#                      Probably use with STRICT
#
#   /defaultcountry g t
#      DRY in /country: just write DEFAULT and get those countries. No special keys like AGGR
#
#	/prefix unstable-u
#      Set prefix
#
#   /range hex-from hex-to
#      Same as hex-from, hex-from+1, etc.
#
#   /fixup hex ALERT
#      Fix up some character, SHOULD EXIST
#      (ranges/lists are created en masse, then bad chars are hand-checked)
#           ALERT          = alert if other character rather than default pops up
#
#   /erase hex
#      Erases a character, UNCHECKED
#
